## Invitation email, also send calendar appointment with text

*Subject line:* Invitation to CMS Demo Environments Training

**Body:**

You are invited to the CMS Demo Environments Training on Thursday, February 11, from 12:00-1:00 p.m. ET.

Please note that live sessions are recorded to capture questions and answers. Please let us know if you have any concerns about attending a recorded session.

Before joining the session, please take a moment to review the information below to prepare for our time together. 

**Date**

Thursday, February 11, from 12:00-1:00 p.m. ET

**Location**

Online via Microsoft Teams (see calendar appointment)

**Before you join**

To make sure you’re able to fully participate in orientation, please take a moment to test Teams.



*   If you haven’t joined a Teams meeting recently, please [try a test meeting](https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/office/manage-your-call-settings-in-teams-456cb611-3477-496f-b31a-6ab752a7595f#:~:text=To%20make%20a%20test%20call,and%20record%20a%20short%20message.).
*   If you have any issues during testing, please visit the [Teams troubleshooting page](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoftteams/troubleshoot/meetings/how-to-join-a-teams-meeting#troubleshooting-meeting-join).
*   A headset is recommended for best audio experience, but is not necessary

If you are using a non-VA laptop for CMS demo environments,  you will need to download the VA Root Certificate Authority in your browser. Please follow the [instructions to do this](https://github.com/department-of-veterans-affairs/va.gov-cms/blob/master/READMES/https.md) prior to the training for a better experience. If you are using a VA laptop, this step isn’t necessary.

**Reasonable accommodation**

Please let us know if you require reasonable accommodation to attend this training.

We’re looking forward to seeing you soon. If you have further questions, please let us know by replying to this email (reply directly -- **please don’t reply all**).

Thank you,


