## Follow-up email - link to questions and answers

Subject: Drupal CMS orientation follow-up + your questions answered

Body:

Dear VA CMS editor, 

Thank you for attending Drupal CMS orientation session 5 and the entire series. The Drupal CMS team is grateful for your time, questions, and willingness to learn as we work together to build Veteran-centered experiences on VA.gov. If you have any feedback on how the training went, we would love to hear from you!

A few items from our time together:

**Your questions, answered** \
If you had a question that we weren’t able to answer during the training, you can now find this information in the Drupal CMS help center, along with training resources from previous sessions.



*   Session 1 the new CMS: https://prod.cms.va.gov/help/session-1-cms-orientation
*   Session 2 editing basics: https://prod.cms.va.gov/help/session-2-editing-basics
*   Session 3 health services: https://prod.cms.va.gov/help/session-3-health-services
*   Session 4 facilities: 

            https://prod.cms.va.gov/help/session-4-facilities

*   Session 5 detail pages, menus and revisions: 

            https://prod.cms.va.gov/help/session-5-detail-pages


If you continue to have questions, please contact our help desk.

**Video coming soon**

We’ll be posting recordings (with captions) of session 5 in the near future. This will include a timestamp guide so you can jump to the relevant parts, and you can come back to it at any time. We will contact everyone via email once that is available. 

**Feedback**

Please share your feedback about the Drupal CMS editorial experience through our survey.



