## Drupal CMS self-service training

Subject: Drupal CMS self-service training now available

Body:

Dear VA CMS editor, 

Welcome to Drupal CMS self-service training. Training is required before you get an account on the production (live) environment.



1. Open a browser to the [training environment](https://cms-training-pion6wlxie1t0mckcgwjl4kid1k1haqe.demo.cms.va.gov/help/access-training#available-trainings) and log in.
*   Username: your VA.gov email address
*   Password: drupal8
*   PIV card login doesn’t work on the training environment.
2. On the CMS help center training page, watch training sessions 1 through 5. When instructed, stop the videos and try the activities.
*   Go as far as you can with each training activity. The training environment is updated more often than the training videos.
*   The training environment isn’t an exact copy of the production environment.
*   The training environment is regularly updated, which deletes training activities.
3. Contact Stan Gardner after watching the training videos and trying the activities in the training environment. He will provide next steps.

Please contact our help desk with any questions or feedback or reply to this email.

Thank you,


