## Training for webmaintainers

Subject: Drupal CMS self-service training now available

Body:

Welcome to Drupal CMS training.

**Complete self-service training for Drupal CMS access**

After you have viewed the training videos and completed the related activities in the training environment, your username for the production (live) environment will be created and emailed to you. 

**View training videos**

Start viewing training videos at [https://prod.cms.va.gov/help/access-training#available-trainings](https://prod.cms.va.gov/help/access-training#available-trainings)

Access to CMS environments and CMS help center require VA network access. If you are still waiting for VA network access, you can get a head start on training by viewing the videos on YouTube:

Session 1 The new CMS: [https://youtu.be/33AXrfGff98](https://youtu.be/33AXrfGff98)

Session 2 Editing basics: [https://youtu.be/cnePWZ7rHpo](https://youtu.be/cnePWZ7rHpo)

**Complete training activities**

Your Drupal CMS training environment username has been created for you. Your username is your current email address. Your PIV card will not work for login to the training environment. 

The default password for training environment accounts is drupal8

Access the Drupal CMS training environment at [http://training.demo.ci.cms.va.gov/](http://training.demo.ci.cms.va.gov/)

Because the training environment is not connected to the live site, it is a safe place for you to try training activities and to explore. Please note that the training environment is occasionally updated, which deletes edited information.

**Resources**

Additional training resources are available in the CMS help center: [https://prod.cms.va.gov/help](https://prod.cms.va.gov/help)

Please reply to this email if you have any questions about training. Our help desk can also be reached at [https://va-gov.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/3](https://va-gov.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/3)

Thank you,

Clarence Maeng, Delivery Manager

VFS-CMS team

_Editor-centered management for Veteran-centered content_


