## CMS Training Environment Link update

Dear Drupal CMS editor:

You may have mistakenly received an email from us with a link to the Drupal CMS production account. Sorry for the confusion - that email was an error.

We want to let you know that URL for the Drupal CMS training environment is changing. 

Starting **Monday, February 15, 2021**, please use this link for Drupal CMS training activities:

[https://cms-training-pion6wlxie1t0mckcgwjl4kid1k1haqe.demo.cms.va.gov/](https://cms-training-pion6wlxie1t0mckcgwjl4kid1k1haqe.demo.cms.va.gov/)

Please update your training environment bookmark if you saved one on your browser.

Your training environment account will be set up on the new training environment. You will log in with your VA.gov email address for the username and use the default password “drupal8”

The Drupal CMS training environment is temporary. It will be refreshed on a regular basis, and at least every Monday at 9:00 a.m. ET, with the latest content and code from the production (live) environment. Any content created or edited directly in the training environment will be lost during the refresh.

Please let us know if you have any questions.

Thank you,
